This is almost exactly how I feel. It's still not quite as visceral or put-together as either of those.

+block

–block


Focusing on the problems:

I kind of expected something to happen with -11 at the end given how he'd been so built up, so that felt like a wasted opportunity.

The letter seems to be set earlier in the story but comes later in the document, which is weird, especially if the letters were supposed to be appearing in 1949 for a specific reason. Also odd that you say  but only give a single letter. The letter itself didn't really add anything to my perspective on them that I hadn't already gotten (and more effectively/emotionally) from the event logs, so it was kind of a waste of space. Honestly, I'd be much more interested in reading a letter with more info on the time after the alliance under -11, or how that developed, or a letter from -11.

Also really odd to have addendum -A when there are -As, and the footnotes were a bit overused and several could be in that text (especially the one to see the addendum. On mobile, clicking bookmarks takes you to the bottom and then you have to scroll back up).

As TL333s said, the letter could use some proofreading. The containment incidents could too. It's really not clear to me why you repeat their designation in the text that is exclusively about them, when you could say 




No vote. At the very least it needs some cleanup, maybe reordering, and hopefully expansion. There's a lot to like here, but it needs more polish.





